-- Police Busts International Gambling Ring, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-12-13T15:00:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/police-busts-international-gambling-ring-xinhua-reports.html
Police from China, Cambodia, Vietnam
and Myanmar jointly broke up an international online gambling
ring with turnover of about 11 billion  yuan  ($1.8 billion),
Xinhua  News Agency  said, citing Chinese police.  Police confiscated more than 32 million yuan of gambling
money and arrested 27 suspects, all Chinese, after an
investigation that lasted more than two years, Xinhua said,
citing police in central Chinaâ€™s Hubei province.  The case involved more than 500 Chinese and foreigners, the
